Definitions
-----------
"Software" means the contents of this repository (source code, binaries,
documentation, and other files) as distributed by the copyright holder.

"Individual" means a natural person acting in their personal capacity and not
acting on behalf of or as a representative of an Organization.

"Organization" means any legal entity or group other than an Individual,
including but not limited to: corporations, limited liability companies,
partnerships, firms, non-profit organizations, government entities, or any
entity that employs, represents or is controlled by multiple persons.

"Commercial use" means any use primarily intended for commercial advantage or
monetary compensation. Commercial use by an Organization includes, but is not
limited to, offering the Software or a derivative as a paid product or service,
incorporating the Software into a product or service that is sold or charged,
or using the Software to provide paid services to customers.

Grant of Rights to Individuals
-------------------------------
Subject to the terms below, the copyright holder hereby grants to any
Individual a worldwide, royalty-free, non-exclusive license to:

  * Use, copy, modify and create derivative works of the Software;
  * Reproduce, distribute, publish or sell copies of the Software or derivative
    works (including for monetary gain), provided the Individual complies with
    the Attribution requirement below.

Grant of Rights to Organizations (Non-Commercial Only)
------------------------------------------------------
Subject to the terms below, the copyright holder hereby grants to Organizations
a worldwide, royalty-free, non-exclusive license to use, copy, modify, and
distribute the Software **only for non-commercial purposes.** Organizations are
strictly prohibited from any Commercial Use of the Software.

Attribution Requirement
-----------------------
Any distribution (source or binary), public display, or publication of the
Software or any derivative work by an Individual or Organization must include
all of the following:

  1. A visible statement that the work is based on "Den 101" by the original
     author;
  2. The original copyright notice:
     "Copyright (c) 2025 CPTicarus";
  3. A link or pointer to the original repository (for example, a GitHub URL).

If the distribution or use is in a medium where a visible statement is
impractical (for example, a small binary splash screen), include the required
attribution in an accompanying text file or documentation.

Prohibited Uses
---------------
Organizations shall not use the Software for Commercial Use. Organizations
shall not sell, sublicense, host as a paid service (SaaS), or otherwise offer
the Software or derivative works for monetary compensation.

Nothing in this license prevents an Organization from informing or offering the
Software to its members or the public for non-commercial purposes (for example,
research, internal evaluation, education, or community development), provided
attribution is preserved.

Reasonable Interpretation and Enforcement
-----------------------------------------
If a question arises whether a use is "Commercial" or whether an entity is an
"Organization", the parties should seek to resolve the matter in good faith;
however the copyright holder reserves the right to take appropriate legal
action to enforce this license.

